        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 4:54PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kingston, or near Genoa, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingston, Genoa, Marengo, Garden Prairie, Kirkland, and Hampshire.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
